course_description: Continuation of Theory,Analysis,Aural Skills I. Applied technical study of harmony and counterpoint focusing on written and aural aspects of the common-practice period but including repertoire from earlier periods and modern times. Designed for music majors and minors.
prerequisites: MUS 121 as prerequisite or equivalent transfer credit.
